metadata.description: sometimes distractions become more amusing than what we originally were seeking. room number is a song i wrote about to express that in the setting of a hotel room. becoming so infatuated with where i am, instead of where i am trying to get to.

lyrics.text:
[Intro/Half Hook]

What’s your room number?
 I forgot it 
I’m still lost in hotel lobbies
 I can’t call you it’s no service up here 

and it’s 5 stars and that’s real nice 
been on the wrong floor all night though 

I can’t find a single person in here 

[Verse]

fuck it I’m lost now
pressin’ every elevator button from the top down 
could sing as loud as I want to in here
and I’m fuckin’ with this four-way mirror
I love just how I look in here 
not saying that I’m happy that I’m lost 

(its kinda fun tough)

[Pre]

pretend I’m sideways
going up, down 
running circles ‘round in this building
but for what now ?
 Im dancing to kill time 
I hope you forgot me 
don’t even need or want the direction 
I’ll be ringing up any second
